# Library Version Management Rules

## Description
Simple rules for managing dependency versions in `libs.versions.toml`

## File Pattern
- `gradle/libs.versions.toml`

## Version Update Rules

### Core Rule
- ONLY update if new version is higher than current version
- NEVER downgrade to lower versions
- Keep current version if new version is equal

### Version Examples
```toml
# CORRECT Updates ✅
1.10.2 -> 1.10.3    # Valid (higher version)
2.0.2 -> 2.1.0      # Valid (higher version)
36 -> 37            # Valid (higher number)

# INCORRECT Updates ❌
4.1.0 -> 4.0.9      # Invalid (lower version)
2.1.21 -> 2.1.21    # Invalid (same version)
36 -> 35            # Invalid (lower number)
```

### Current Base Versions
```toml
# Reference versions - Update only if higher
agp = "8.8.2"
